name: FedEx 767-300F [N123FE] Pre-Delivery Flight Testing at Paine Field
description:
Some more footage from my 2015 trip to Paine Field! Here we have a now-delivered FedEx 767 Freighter undergoing some flight testing at Everett's Paine Field, taking off, landing, and then taking off again on a different date. Enjoy!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFO
Airline: Federal Express (FDX/FX)
Aircraft: Boeing 767-3S2(F) (B763)
Aircraft Name: "Shuler"
Livery: Standard
Engines: 2x GE CF6-80C2B6F 
Registration: N123FE
Route: Paine Field (PAE) - Moses Lake (MWH) - Paine Field (PAE)
Callsign: Boeing ???
Runway used: 16R
Date filmed: July 2015
